12
00:01:41,976 --> 00:01:44,216
Looking for pupils.

13
00:01:44,336 --> 00:01:45,896
But no luck,

14
00:01:46,016 --> 00:01:48,336
I couldn't find any.

15
00:01:48,736 --> 00:01:50,736
I was there for three days.

16
00:01:50,856 --> 00:01:52,736
- Cigarette?
- No thanks.

17
00:01:52,856 --> 00:01:55,056
I don't smoke.

18
00:01:56,496 --> 00:01:57,896
You couldn't find any pupils?

19
00:01:58,016 --> 00:01:59,536
Not one.

20
00:02:01,536 --> 00:02:04,416
My father warned me

21
00:02:04,776 --> 00:02:07,616
but I didn't listen to him

22
00:02:07,736 --> 00:02:09,296
and now,

23
00:02:09,616 --> 00:02:13,016
I truly regret it.

24
00:02:13,136 --> 00:02:14,976
- You studied for long?
- Two years.

25
00:02:15,096 --> 00:02:17,496
You became a teacher in two years?

26
00:02:17,616 --> 00:02:19,536
I worked hard.

27
00:02:19,656 --> 00:02:21,696
- You like it?
- Not really.

28
00:02:21,816 --> 00:02:22,776
Why?

29
00:02:22,896 --> 00:02:26,936
I looked for three days
and I found nothing.

30
00:02:28,896 --> 00:02:31,096
I didn't listen to my father.

31
00:02:33,176 --> 00:02:37,496
- What did he tell you to do?
- To be a shepherd.

32
00:02:37,696 --> 00:02:39,496
I failed.

33
00:04:29,536 --> 00:04:31,256
He's gone.

34
00:04:31,376 --> 00:04:32,976
Get up.

35
00:04:37,336 --> 00:04:39,496
Hurry up!

36
00:04:52,976 --> 00:04:53,896
And your wife?

37
00:04:54,016 --> 00:04:58,136
When we got back from Tehran,
we had a fight

38
00:04:58,616 --> 00:05:02,216
about the doctor.

39
00:05:02,336 --> 00:05:05,256
Her family insulted my family.
Mine responded in kind.

40
00:05:05,376 --> 00:05:08,216
So her father took her.

41
00:05:08,336 --> 00:05:10,016
Hurry up.
We have to hide him.

42
00:05:10,256 --> 00:05:12,136
It's been three months

43
00:05:12,296 --> 00:05:13,936
since she went back with her father.

44
00:05:14,056 --> 00:05:17,136
She left me with three kids,
one of them just a baby

45
00:05:17,256 --> 00:05:19,256
I tried to find him a wet nurse.

46
00:05:19,776 --> 00:05:23,616
I went through a hundred families

47
00:05:23,736 --> 00:05:26,136
to find one.

48
00:05:26,256 --> 00:05:28,736
As a result

49
00:05:29,056 --> 00:05:31,856
he's drunk the milk of many women,
even cows

50
00:05:32,896 --> 00:05:36,256
He looks like
a hundred different women.

51
00:05:36,416 --> 00:05:39,736
He's got the eyes of one,
the ears of another.

52
00:05:39,856 --> 00:05:42,096
And he's sick.

53
00:05:42,216 --> 00:05:44,656
Now I run from village to village

54
00:05:44,776 --> 00:05:47,696
looking for a pupil
I can make into a doctor.

55
00:05:47,896 --> 00:05:51,576
That way,
we'd never have to go into town.

56
00:05:51,696 --> 00:05:53,576
If there was a doctor
in the next village

57
00:05:53,696 --> 00:05:56,136
things would be easier.

58
00:05:58,056 --> 00:06:01,056
- You're going to make a doctor?
- Yes.

59
00:06:36,096 --> 00:06:38,616
- Which path are you taking?
- The one on the right.

60
00:06:39,376 --> 00:06:41,376
It's dangerous.

61
00:06:43,376 --> 00:06:45,176
- Which way are you going?
- This way.

62
00:06:45,296 --> 00:06:47,736
But it's very dangerous.

63
00:06:50,176 --> 00:06:52,856
Wait.

64
00:06:54,256 --> 00:06:56,496
I'll tell you again,
it's a death trap.

65
00:06:56,616 --> 00:06:58,656
Yours is even worse.

66
00:06:58,776 --> 00:07:02,216
No. Yours is more dangerous.
Goodbye.

67
00:07:03,976 --> 00:07:06,656
- Where are you going now?
- to the village.

68
00:07:07,096 --> 00:07:09,576
- Can I come with you?
- If you like.

69
00:07:09,696 --> 00:07:12,736
If we go together do you think
we'll find any pupils?

70
00:07:13,256 --> 00:07:14,736
- I'm not coming.
- Why?

71
00:07:14,936 --> 00:07:16,656
I want to go to the top.

72
00:07:18,976 --> 00:07:21,176
- How many pupils will you find?
- Two or three.

73
00:07:21,296 --> 00:07:23,096
Fine. Keep them.

74
00:07:23,376 --> 00:07:25,296
I'm going to climb to the very top.

75
00:07:30,296 --> 00:07:32,696
The villages bring me bad luck.

76
00:07:32,816 --> 00:07:34,336
My fortune lies up there.

77
00:07:34,456 --> 00:07:38,176
Go on, you take the villages.
I'm going up there.

78
00:07:38,296 --> 00:07:39,296
Goodbye.

79
00:07:41,336 --> 00:07:42,816
Take care.

80
00:08:28,416 --> 00:08:29,816
Hello!

81
00:08:30,736 --> 00:08:32,216
Hello!

82
00:08:35,416 --> 00:08:37,616
Is there a school here?

83
00:08:37,736 --> 00:08:39,536
I don't know.

84
00:08:40,496 --> 00:08:42,616
And a teacher?

85
00:08:43,016 --> 00:08:44,496
I don't know.

86
00:08:45,416 --> 00:08:47,616
No idea.

87
00:08:48,616 --> 00:08:49,496
Goodbye.

88
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:51,856
- And I'm sorry.
- The Lord will go with you.

89
00:08:52,576 --> 00:08:54,216
Excuse me!

90
00:08:54,536 --> 00:08:56,416
Wait a minute.

91
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:57,776
What?

92
00:09:05,936 --> 00:09:08,976
Please, read me this letter.

93
00:09:17,536 --> 00:09:17,976
What is it?

94
00:09:19,456 --> 00:09:21,376
What does he say?

95
00:09:23,576 --> 00:09:25,656
Hold on.

96
00:09:28,576 --> 00:09:30,616
This letter isn't in Persian.

97
00:09:31,256 --> 00:09:32,496
Where does it come from?

98
00:09:32,656 --> 00:09:35,656
For the love of God, read it to me.

99
00:09:37,576 --> 00:09:39,016
It's from your son?
It's not in Persian. Maybe Arabic?

100
00:09:44,376 --> 00:09:45,256
Where's it from?

101
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:47,656
From Iraq.

102
00:09:48,976 --> 00:09:53,696
I don't know if it's in Arabic,
Turkish or Kurdish.

103
00:09:54,576 --> 00:09:56,216
It's from my son.

104
00:09:57,176 --> 00:10:00,176
