127
00:13:11,176 --> 00:13:14,536
The goats go up this way?

128
00:13:16,736 --> 00:13:19,216
Listen, I am a teacher.

129
00:13:19,816 --> 00:13:21,536
- What?
- I am a teacher.

130
00:13:21,656 --> 00:13:24,616
So what are you doing here?

131
00:13:25,056 --> 00:13:27,856
- Looking for children.
- Good luck.

132
00:13:28,336 --> 00:13:31,016
- Where are they?
- Up there.

133
00:13:31,136 --> 00:13:33,456
Listen, young man,
I'm talking to you.

134
00:13:33,576 --> 00:13:35,536
I've already told you,
they're up there.

135
00:13:36,256 --> 00:13:38,536
- Which way should I go?
- The way I told you.

136
00:13:38,656 --> 00:13:40,576
Straight ahead.

137
00:13:43,616 --> 00:13:44,496
Do you know how to write?

138
00:13:47,456 --> 00:13:49,136
Do you know how to write?

139
00:13:50,656 --> 00:13:51,816
To read and write?

140
00:13:51,936 --> 00:13:53,096
No.

141
00:13:53,736 --> 00:13:55,536
Would you like to learn?

142
00:13:56,256 --> 00:13:57,536
It's useless.

143
00:13:57,736 --> 00:13:59,416
Show me the way.

144
00:13:59,536 --> 00:14:01,376
The way, young man!

145
00:14:03,696 --> 00:14:05,176
Where are you going?

146
00:14:07,736 --> 00:14:09,136
- Young Man!
- What?

147
00:14:09,256 --> 00:14:10,176
The way?

148
00:14:10,296 --> 00:14:13,296
Here. There. Also here.

149
00:14:14,136 --> 00:14:15,656
Not this way?

150
00:14:16,056 --> 00:14:17,616
I'm talking to you!

151
00:14:17,736 --> 00:14:19,496
- Young man!
- What?

152
00:14:20,296 --> 00:14:22,136
Show me the way.

153
00:14:22,496 --> 00:14:25,736
I want you to show me the way.
Look at me!

154
00:14:25,896 --> 00:14:27,616
Leave me alone.

155
00:14:29,736 --> 00:14:31,176
Anybody here?

156
00:14:32,376 --> 00:14:34,136
Anybody here?

157
00:14:34,296 --> 00:14:36,536
Is there anyone here?

158
00:14:39,136 --> 00:14:43,136
Open the windows.
Answer me!

159
00:14:49,576 --> 00:14:52,336
Multiplication tables!

160
00:14:54,296 --> 00:14:56,856
Come and learn how to multiply.

161
00:14:58,896 --> 00:15:00,616
One times two is two.

162
00:15:01,496 --> 00:15:04,416
Two times two is four.

163
00:15:07,536 --> 00:15:08,856
Madame!

164
00:15:10,256 --> 00:15:12,456
Do you need a teacher?

165
00:15:12,576 --> 00:15:14,976
- What?
- I am a teacher.

166
00:15:15,296 --> 00:15:16,936
Where are your children?

167
00:15:17,056 --> 00:15:19,336
Leave me alone.

168
00:15:23,056 --> 00:15:25,416
- I have come to teach your children.
- I am a teacher.

169
00:15:25,536 --> 00:15:27,456
- Who are you?
- I'm looking for pupils.

170
00:15:27,656 --> 00:15:30,296
Good for you.

171
00:15:31,456 --> 00:15:34,176
Where are the children?

172
00:15:36,136 --> 00:15:37,776
Go away.

173
00:15:59,896 --> 00:16:01,616
Anybody here?

174
00:16:02,576 --> 00:16:04,416
Anybody here?

175
00:16:04,696 --> 00:16:06,736
Is there anyone here?

176
00:16:07,656 --> 00:16:11,096
I can hear voices.

177
00:16:11,616 --> 00:16:13,736
I've come a long way

178
00:16:13,936 --> 00:16:15,656
to teach your children

179
00:16:15,896 --> 00:16:19,456
to read and write.

180
00:16:19,736 --> 00:16:22,816
You won't need to pay me much.

181
00:16:24,416 --> 00:16:27,296
I'll teach you to read
and write letters.

182
00:16:50,496 --> 00:16:53,776
Children, at last!
Wonderful! Come here.

183
00:16:55,016 --> 00:16:58,176
Stop.
Tell me where you've come from.

184
00:16:58,456 --> 00:16:59,416
Where have you come from?

185
00:17:01,056 --> 00:17:02,816
Where are you going?

186
00:17:03,656 --> 00:17:05,416
Where have you come from?

187
00:17:09,056 --> 00:17:12,456
I've come from deep in the valley
to find you.

188
00:17:12,576 --> 00:17:14,696
Let us through, mister.

189
00:17:16,336 --> 00:17:17,816
Just a moment.

190
00:17:17,936 --> 00:17:19,856
I'm not going to eat you.

191
00:17:20,016 --> 00:17:23,176
I only want to talk to you.

192
00:17:24,216 --> 00:17:26,896
- Do you have a school here?
- No.

193
00:17:27,856 --> 00:17:30,416
- And a teacher?
- No.

194
00:17:30,736 --> 00:17:32,816
- Would you like one?
- No.

195
00:17:33,016 --> 00:17:35,736
Where are you going
with those burdens?

196
00:17:35,856 --> 00:17:38,176
- We're mules.
- What?

197
00:17:38,576 --> 00:17:41,176
- Then I'll come with you. OK?
- No.

198
00:17:41,336 --> 00:17:43,376
Let us get past, mister.

199
00:17:43,816 --> 00:17:45,856
Let us get past!

200
00:17:46,176 --> 00:17:47,896
Wait a minute, kid!

201
00:17:48,416 --> 00:17:51,616
Allow me to finish
and I'll let you go.

202
00:17:52,456 --> 00:17:55,976
Just one question:
where are you going with those?

203
00:17:56,256 --> 00:17:58,096
Let us get past!

204
00:17:58,536 --> 00:18:01,336
It's heavy!
You can't stay there like that.

205
00:18:01,576 --> 00:18:02,856
Let us get past.

206
00:18:03,496 --> 00:18:04,536
We're wiped out.

207
00:18:04,696 --> 00:18:07,016
- You don't have a teacher?
- No.

208
00:18:07,576 --> 00:18:08,936
There's no teachers here.

209
00:18:09,056 --> 00:18:11,376
- Where are you going?
- I don't know.

210
00:18:11,656 --> 00:18:12,656
You don't know?

211
00:18:13,536 --> 00:18:15,896
Let us pass,
we're wiped out.

212
00:18:16,336 --> 00:18:17,936
Look.

213
00:18:18,576 --> 00:18:20,736
You're holding us all up.

214
00:18:22,096 --> 00:18:23,136
Let us pass.

215
00:18:55,456 --> 00:18:57,936
I'm a teacher

216
00:18:58,616 --> 00:19:02,016
and I've come to teach you
to read and write.

217
00:19:02,336 --> 00:19:04,536
I've come a long way.

218
00:19:04,976 --> 00:19:07,776
I've been looking for you
for a long time!

219
00:19:08,976 --> 00:19:13,176
I want to teach you
to read and write,

220
00:19:14,136 --> 00:19:17,656
to add up and multiply.

221
00:19:18,816 --> 00:19:21,336
I don't want a lot of money

222
00:19:21,456 --> 00:19:22,696
if you don't have any,

223
00:19:23,456 --> 00:19:26,856
you could just give me
something to eat.

224
00:19:27,376 --> 00:19:30,776
We carry contraband, stolen goods.

225
00:19:31,016 --> 00:19:33,656
We take it

226
00:19:34,736 --> 00:19:38,976
over the border

227
00:19:39,296 --> 00:19:41,576
between Iran and Iraq.

228
00:19:41,696 --> 00:19:44,256
We're always on the run.

229
00:19:45,696 --> 00:19:47,256
Listen, my child.

230
00:19:47,416 --> 00:19:49,216
With education,

231
00:19:49,376 --> 00:19:51,976
you will be able to read a book

232
00:19:52,456 --> 00:19:55,896
or, even better, a newspaper

233
00:19:56,016 --> 00:19:58,576
when you're travelling.

234
00:19:58,696 --> 00:20:00,576
Learn to read and write!

235
00:20:00,696 --> 00:20:03,736
You'll know what's going on
in the world.

236
00:20:04,856 --> 00:20:08,256
You can learn to add up,

237
00:20:08,736 --> 00:20:12,096
to substract, to do your accounts
without being swindled.

238
00:20:12,576 --> 00:20:16,096
What good is it, all that?

239
00:20:16,576 --> 00:20:19,296
You could study or find work

240
00:20:23,256 --> 00:20:25,416
Doing the accounts,

241
00:20:25,536 --> 00:20:27,456
that's great for the Boss.

242
00:20:27,576 --> 00:20:29,456
Us, we're mules.

243
00:20:30,016 --> 00:20:32,136
Always on the move.

244
00:20:32,296 --> 00:20:34,856
How do you expect us to read?

245
00:20:34,976 --> 00:20:38,256
To read a book,

246
00:20:38,456 --> 00:20:40,256
you have to sit down.

247
00:20:40,416 --> 00:20:43,056
Us, we never stop moving.

248
00:20:56,016 --> 00:20:59,776
Listen, I want to talk to you.

249
00:21:00,736 --> 00:21:02,256
Stop! Wait!

250
00:21:02,656 --> 00:21:04,896
Wait!

251
00:21:17,176 --> 00:21:18,656
Hello.

252
00:21:19,456 --> 00:21:21,616
Do you know how to read and write?

253
00:21:22,336 --> 00:21:24,656
- Do you?
- No.

254
00:21:24,856 --> 00:21:27,416
- Do you want to learn?
- No.

255
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:29,256
- You don't?
- No.

256
00:21:30,616 --> 00:21:32,016
Hello.

257
00:21:33,256 --> 00:21:35,176
Do you know how to read and write?

258
00:21:36,416 --> 00:21:38,576
- Do you?
- No.

259
00:21:44,656 --> 00:21:46,176
Hello, sir!

260
00:21:47,016 --> 00:21:49,096
- I'm talking to you.
- What?

261
00:21:49,416 --> 00:21:50,976
You wouldn't have a scrap of bread?

262
00:21:51,296 --> 00:21:53,456
It's freezing!

263
00:21:53,736 --> 00:21:55,816
Where are you going?

264
00:21:56,736 --> 00:21:59,456
I don't have a job,
can I come with you?

265
00:21:59,576 --> 00:22:01,536
We don't need you.

266
00:22:10,136 --> 00:22:12,816
Hello. How's it going?

267
00:22:13,896 --> 00:22:16,016
It's freezing!

268
00:22:18,256 --> 00:22:19,896
Hello, sir.

269
00:22:20,456 --> 00:22:21,936
Sir!

270
00:22:25,376 --> 00:22:26,816
I'm talking to you.

271
00:22:27,016 --> 00:22:30,896
Why won't you answer me?

272
00:22:32,096 --> 00:22:34,936
Haven't you got any work for me?

273
00:22:35,056 --> 00:22:36,496
No.

274
00:22:36,616 --> 00:22:38,776
