Look at my blackboard!

551
00:50:45,416 --> 00:50:49,416
I want ot teach you
to read and write.

552
00:50:49,536 --> 00:50:52,096
Watch me! Listen to me!

553
00:50:53,096 --> 00:50:54,576
Don't listen to him.

554
00:50:54,696 --> 00:50:56,696
Let's get out of here!

555
00:50:56,816 --> 00:50:59,416
Let's go! Carry him.

556
00:50:59,536 --> 00:51:01,576
Children! Where are you going?

557
00:51:04,216 --> 00:51:05,296
Stop!

558
00:51:06,816 --> 00:51:08,696
Listen to me!

559
00:51:11,256 --> 00:51:13,056
Don't go!

560
00:51:14,016 --> 00:51:17,096
It's your fault, all this!

561
00:51:19,216 --> 00:51:20,656
Children!

562
00:51:47,016 --> 00:51:49,456
- Repeat.
- Did I say it right?

563
00:51:49,576 --> 00:51:51,096
Well done.

564
00:51:55,656 --> 00:51:56,816
Very good.

565
00:51:58,776 --> 00:52:00,456
Stretch out the R...

566
00:52:01,896 --> 00:52:04,576
R like Reeboir.

567
00:52:05,496 --> 00:52:07,496
Listen, friend.

568
00:52:09,736 --> 00:52:13,536
What happened:
we chased the rabbit,

569
00:52:13,656 --> 00:52:16,536
we caught it

570
00:52:16,656 --> 00:52:19,696
and we ate it.

571
00:52:19,816 --> 00:52:21,856
It was tasty!

572
00:52:21,976 --> 00:52:23,376
Delicious!

573
00:53:38,376 --> 00:53:39,656
A like Apple...

574
00:53:42,296 --> 00:53:46,616
Be quiet.
They're behind us.

575
00:53:46,736 --> 00:53:50,576
Reeboir and his group, this way.

576
00:53:50,696 --> 00:53:53,896
Group two, take the other path.

577
00:53:56,256 --> 00:53:57,816
The rest of you, follow me.

578
00:53:58,256 --> 00:54:00,456
Be careful. It's dangerous.

579
00:54:15,496 --> 00:54:20,016
Not this way!
There are landmines everywhere!

580
00:54:20,416 --> 00:54:25,016
Take the other path.

581
00:54:25,536 --> 00:54:29,656
Look out!

582
00:54:29,776 --> 00:54:33,256
Don't get yourselves killed.

583
00:54:34,176 --> 00:54:37,696
Go round the other side!

584
00:55:13,096 --> 00:55:14,736
Two times two?

585
00:55:15,776 --> 00:55:17,176
Four.

586
00:55:17,656 --> 00:55:19,376
Reply!

587
00:55:19,936 --> 00:55:22,216
Reply swiftly, learn swiftly.

588
00:55:22,896 --> 00:55:24,536
Two times three?

589
00:55:25,576 --> 00:55:27,216
Six.

590
00:55:29,176 --> 00:55:30,856
Four times two?

591
00:55:33,936 --> 00:55:37,216
Come on, answer!

592
00:55:38,616 --> 00:55:40,216
Two times five?

593
00:55:41,576 --> 00:55:44,096
Come on: ten!

594
00:55:44,256 --> 00:55:47,456
To learn quickly
you must answer quickly.

595
00:55:48,576 --> 00:55:50,096
One times two?

596
00:55:50,336 --> 00:55:52,256
Two.

597
00:55:53,096 --> 00:55:54,696
Two times two? Four.

598
00:55:55,016 --> 00:55:58,456
One times two? Two.

599
00:56:08,656 --> 00:56:10,536
Mother, a rabbit!

600
00:56:30,736 --> 00:56:32,056
Chuan!

601
00:56:32,176 --> 00:56:35,416
What are you doing?
The Devil take you!

602
00:56:37,816 --> 00:56:39,216
Halaleh!

603
00:56:41,536 --> 00:56:44,416
Where is she gone?

604
00:56:59,696 --> 00:57:02,016
The Devil take you!

605
00:57:07,096 --> 00:57:08,336
Halaleh!

606
00:57:10,656 --> 00:57:13,416
Where are you?

607
00:57:24,416 --> 00:57:28,296
Please, sir,
have you seen my wife?

608
00:57:47,176 --> 00:57:49,856
Where are you going?

609
00:57:50,176 --> 00:57:51,896
Stop...

610
00:58:01,976 --> 00:58:03,656
You want some walnuts?

611
00:58:11,456 --> 00:58:13,496
One times two is two!

612
00:58:19,176 --> 00:58:21,456
Why are you running away?

613
00:58:22,456 --> 00:58:25,576
Have I done something wrong?

614
00:58:25,936 --> 00:58:27,856
If maths is too difficult,

615
00:58:27,976 --> 00:58:31,816
I'll teach you to read.

616
00:58:31,936 --> 00:58:35,056
Repeat after me...

617
00:58:36,336 --> 00:58:39,616
"I love you"

618
00:58:39,736 --> 00:58:41,656
See, it's easy.

619
00:58:44,256 --> 00:58:45,656
Say it!

620
00:58:46,256 --> 00:58:49,496
Come on, say it!

621
00:58:49,616 --> 00:58:53,376
Say "I love you".

622
00:58:53,496 --> 00:58:54,416
Look at me.

623
00:59:00,056 --> 00:59:03,656
What sort of student are you?

624
00:59:03,776 --> 00:59:06,216
I'll give you eight.

625
00:59:08,856 --> 00:59:11,536
No, not eight.

626
00:59:11,656 --> 00:59:13,176
That would fail you.

627
00:59:13,296 --> 00:59:17,056
I'll give you ten,

628
00:59:20,136 --> 00:59:22,016
so you pass.

629
00:59:22,216 --> 00:59:23,816
Say it!

630
00:59:24,536 --> 00:59:26,736
Say "I love you".

631
00:59:26,856 --> 00:59:28,416
You don't want to?

632
00:59:29,376 --> 00:59:30,936
What sort of student are you?

633
00:59:32,856 --> 00:59:35,536
I'm giving you zero.

634
00:59:39,096 --> 00:59:41,616
At least say that you don't love me.

635
00:59:43,896 --> 00:59:45,576
What's wrong?

636
00:59:47,656 --> 00:59:49,776
You won't say that either?

637
00:59:51,976 --> 00:59:53,736
Here comes another zero.

638
00:59:55,616 --> 00:59:57,216
Happy now?

639
00:59:58,296 --> 01:00:00,856
Now a zero for your son.

640
01:00:02,616 --> 01:00:04,416
Here's a zero for your son.

641
01:00:06,056 --> 01:00:07,216
What?

642
01:00:08,536 --> 01:00:13,336
You still won't answer?
I'll give you a zero for your father.

643
01:00:14,936 --> 01:00:16,096
Here.

644
01:00:23,656 --> 01:00:26,536
Still got nothing to say?

645
01:00:26,656 --> 01:00:30,496
I'll give myself a zero.

646
01:00:31,216 --> 01:00:33,816
For having been stupid enough
to follow you.

647
01:00:33,936 --> 01:00:36,496
What kind of a life is this?

648
01:00:36,856 --> 01:00:39,216
Goodbye.

649
01:00:43,736 --> 01:00:45,616
How could I have loved you?

650
01:00:45,856 --> 01:00:47,416
You're not listening to me!

651
01:00:52,376 --> 01:00:54,176
Blackboard!

652
01:00:55,656 --> 01:00:57,056
Stop!

653
01:00:57,416 --> 01:00:59,336
Blackboard!

654
01:01:02,576 --> 01:01:03,976
Stop.

655
01:01:15,856 --> 01:01:19,296
Listen!

656
01:01:32,416 --> 01:01:35,496
My heart is like a train.

657
01:01:35,616 --> 01:01:40,056
At every station,
someone gets on or off.

658
01:01:40,176 --> 01:01:43,896
But there is someone
who never gets off.

659
01:01:45,376 --> 01:01:46,616
My son.

660
01:01:51,216 --> 01:01:52,496
Halaleh...

661
01:01:54,296 --> 01:01:56,176
What's happening?

662
01:02:14,816 --> 01:02:16,816
Escape! Hurry up!

663
01:02:17,456 --> 01:02:19,056
What's going on?

664
01:02:27,616 --> 01:02:32,256
The soldiers at the border
have opened fire!

665
01:04:04,616 --> 01:04:05,976
A like Apple.

666
01:04:07,976 --> 01:04:10,216
Break the syllables up.

667
01:04:32,336 --> 01:04:35,896
Excuse me, Sir. I'm sorry.

668
01:04:36,256 --> 01:04:39,936
We're in danger.
I'll come back later.

669
01:06:29,336 --> 01:06:30,816
Halt!

670
01:06:31,176 --> 01:06:33,696
Who goes there?

671
01:07:06,336 --> 01:07:08,016
What's your name?

672
01:07:09,096 --> 01:07:11,416
- You don't want to tell me?
- Ghazal.

673
01:07:13,656 --> 01:07:16,376
Do you know how to read and write?

674
01:07:18,176 --> 01:07:20,336
- Do you?
No.

675
01:07:21,496 --> 01:07:23,976
- Where is your village?
- Down there.

676
01:07:24,096 --> 01:07:26,736
- That's Dezl?
- Yes.

677
01:07:26,856 --> 01:07:29,696
- Is there a school?
- No.

678
01:07:30,856 --> 01:07:32,856
- Do you want a teacher?
- No.

679
01:08:03,616 --> 01:08:06,376
- Will we have to wait long?
- Who knows.

680
01:08:06,496 --> 01:08:07,776
Where are your friends?

681
01:08:07,896 --> 01:08:10,576
We're meeting up by the river.

682
01:08:10,696 --> 01:08:13,736
No, it was near the goats.

683
01:08:13,856 --> 01:08:16,816
- They're not coming.
- They've been caught.

684
01:08:25,856 --> 01:08:29,936
Thanks for the milk. Excellent.

685
01:08:57,616 --> 01:09:00,576
Sir, I've written something.
- What?

686
01:09:03,496 --> 01:09:05,256
- I wrote something.
- What?

687
01:09:05,376 --> 01:09:07,456
- I wrote my name.
- Well done.

688
01:09:07,576 --> 01:09:09,016
I wrote Reeboir.

689
01:09:11,216 --> 01:09:13,456
Run for your life!

690
01:09:40,096 --> 01:09:41,376
Take him.

691
01:09:41,496 --> 01:09:42,696
Come.

692
01:09:44,816 --> 01:09:46,136
Quick.

693
01:09:49,536 --> 01:09:51,176
It's just like at Halebtcheh...

694
01:09:57,576 --> 01:10:00,536
I built a wall to protect us

695
01:10:01,776 --> 01:10:03,416
from chemical weapons.

696
01:10:08,696 --> 01:10:10,056
Father!

697
01:10:15,936 --> 01:10:18,536
Chemical weapons...

698
01:10:24,296 --> 01:10:25,656
Father!

699
01:10:41,136 --> 01:10:42,456
Look after him.

700
01:10:57,896 --> 01:10:59,136
Chemical weapons...

701
01:10:59,416 --> 01:11:00,656
What's happened?

702
01:11:02,016 --> 01:11:04,136
I pissed.

703
01:11:08,496 --> 01:11:10,256
Hide under the blackboard.

704
01:11:14,816 --> 01:11:17,176
My daughter!

705
01:11:27,336 --> 01:11:30,936
Your brother is dead. Let's go.
He wanted to die in his homeland.

706
01:11:31,056 --> 01:11:35,416
He isn't dead.

707
01:11:37,096 --> 01:11:39,376
Come on. He is dead.

708
01:12:04,656 --> 01:12:07,136
- Just like at Halebtcheh.
- It's rifle fire.

709
01:12:08,016 --> 01:12:11,336
It's not chemical weapons.

710
01:12:11,456 --> 01:12:14,896
Don't worry.

711
01:12:15,016 --> 01:12:19,096
It's the soldiers
from over the border

712
01:12:19,576 --> 01:12:22,376
who were firing.

713
01:12:23,696 --> 01:12:26,776
It's not chemical weapons.

714
01:12:28,536 --> 01:12:32,856
Don't be afraid, my darling.

715
01:12:36,336 --> 01:12:38,096
The women...

716
01:12:38,256 --> 01:12:40,216
The children...

717
01:12:46,456 --> 01:12:49,336
We're not going to die.

718
01:12:50,176 --> 01:12:52,936
It's not chemical weapons.

719
01:12:53,056 --> 01:12:54,976
It's the soldiers, over the border.

720
01:12:55,096 --> 01:12:58,976
If you hear us, they'll fire.

721
01:12:59,216 --> 01:13:01,056
I swear, it's not chemical weapons.

722
01:13:05,856 --> 01:13:07,576
The women...

723
01:13:07,856 --> 01:13:09,536
The men...

724
01:13:27,936 --> 01:13:29,816
Hide under the blackboard.

725
01:13:36,936 --> 01:13:39,696
I'll protect you.

726
01:14:31,376 --> 01:14:33,096
Strop!

727
01:14:37,016 --> 01:14:40,856
There. The border.

728
01:14:40,976 --> 01:14:42,656
The land of your fathers,

729
01:14:42,776 --> 01:14:44,856
of your ancestors.

730
01:14:44,976 --> 01:14:46,816
Your homeland!

731
01:14:46,936 --> 01:14:49,536
You're lying!

732
01:14:49,656 --> 01:14:52,256
I swear I'm not.

733
01:14:52,416 --> 01:14:55,616
It's the truth. Take a good look.

734
01:14:55,736 --> 01:14:57,816
Don't you recognise Halebtcheh?

735
01:14:57,936 --> 01:15:00,136
No. It's not the border.

736
01:15:00,256 --> 01:15:03,336
He's tricked us, I know it.

737
01:15:03,456 --> 01:15:07,376
He's lying.
It's not the border.

738
01:15:07,496 --> 01:15:12,216
We are lost.

739
01:15:12,456 --> 01:15:15,336
I know our border very well.
This isn't it.

740
01:15:15,456 --> 01:15:17,896
I'm not lying.

741
01:15:18,016 --> 01:15:20,056
I swear to you this is it.

742
01:15:20,176 --> 01:15:23,176
This is your homeland.

743
01:15:23,296 --> 01:15:26,936
This isn't the border!
We are lost!

744
01:15:27,056 --> 01:15:29,616
Can't you understand?

745
01:15:36,496 --> 01:15:37,496
Don't you believe me?

746
01:15:37,656 --> 01:15:41,536
You're lying.
You've tricked us, Blackboard!

747
01:15:42,136 --> 01:15:43,856
I swear to you, I'm not lying.

748
01:15:43,976 --> 01:15:46,536
It's been like this
since the bombing.

749
01:15:49,816 --> 01:15:52,176
It's not true!

750
01:15:52,296 --> 01:15:55,296
I swear to you, this is the border.

751
01:15:58,536 --> 01:16:01,776
You're looking at Halebtcheh.

752
01:16:02,256 --> 01:16:06,216
It's because of the bombing...

753
01:16:44,216 --> 01:16:46,456
God be praised!

754
01:17:30,256 --> 01:17:33,736
We are grateful to you.
Here are the nuts.

755
01:17:34,256 --> 01:17:36,376
What will you do now?

756
01:17:36,496 --> 01:17:38,776
Will you cross the border with us?

757
01:17:38,896 --> 01:17:40,816
No, I can't.

758
01:17:40,936 --> 01:17:45,056
but your wife wants to cross over.
She won't stay with you.

759
01:17:45,176 --> 01:17:46,576
What's your decision?

760
01:17:46,696 --> 01:17:50,496
If she doesn't want me,
what can I do?

761
01:17:50,616 --> 01:17:52,936
I don't know. You must decide.

762
01:17:53,056 --> 01:17:54,256
A divorce?

763
01:17:54,376 --> 01:17:56,496
Yes, if that's what she wants.

764
01:17:56,616 --> 01:17:58,696
Let's find out.

765
01:18:00,136 --> 01:18:03,696
Are you coming with us, Blackboard?

766
01:18:03,816 --> 01:18:06,496
I can't.
I belong here, in this land.

767
01:18:07,056 --> 01:18:10,576
Your wife wants to return
to her country. She doesn't want you.

768
01:18:10,696 --> 01:18:12,456
Did she tell you that?

769
01:18:15,856 --> 01:18:19,136
There's nothing I can do.
I'll divorce her.

770
01:18:19,256 --> 01:18:21,616
- You will divorce her?
- Yes.

771
01:18:22,216 --> 01:18:24,816
Go and find her.

772
01:18:32,456 --> 01:18:34,256
Put it down here.

773
01:18:37,336 --> 01:18:40,536
Do you agree to a divorce?

774
01:18:40,736 --> 01:18:44,696
And that you will take
the blackboard?

775
01:18:44,816 --> 01:18:46,656
The blackboard? Yes.

776
01:18:46,776 --> 01:18:49,856
You may look at each other

777
01:18:49,976 --> 01:18:52,016
one last time.

778
01:18:52,136 --> 01:18:53,976
Lift your hand.

779
01:18:54,936 --> 01:18:56,656
Take that stick.

780
01:18:57,856 --> 01:18:59,376
Halaleh,

781
01:18:59,496 --> 01:19:01,176
you are now divorced,

782
01:19:01,456 --> 01:19:05,976
and the blackboard is yours.

783
01:19:06,696 --> 01:19:10,056
May God keep you from hunger!

784
01:19:10,176 --> 01:19:12,536
May God keep you from thirst!

785
01:19:12,656 --> 01:19:15,496
May God keep you from solitude!

786
01:19:19,576 --> 01:19:22,016
Take your blackboard.

787
01:19:22,736 --> 01:19:25,816
And give me my stick.

788
01:19:25,936 --> 01:19:27,536
Goodbye.

789
01:19:34,336 --> 01:19:37,456
I love you.

790
01:19:44,296 --> 01:19:46,936
Chuan! What are you doing?

791
01:19:47,056 --> 01:19:50,176
Hurry up. Come on.

792
01:19:54,176 --> 01:19:56,696
Come, quickly.

